<section id="data-features">
<title>Feature Summary</title>

<variableList>
<varListEntry>
<term><emphasis>Requirement:</emphasis>Data should be collected from the resources and moved away from the resource to be stored.</term>
<listItem>
<para>
	<itemizedList>
	<listItem>
		<para>The depot runs separate from the reporter manager and communicates
		with other components of the Inca system through the network.  The depot component should be installed on non-compute resources
		with database capabilities.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	</itemizedList>
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>

<varListEntry>
<term><emphasis>Requirement:</emphasis>Installation, setup, and maintenance of
the Inca deployment should be simple.  For the data collection this implies
that the addition of new data should require no configuration.</term>
<listItem>
<para>
	<itemizedList>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		The data in a reporter is self describing and the depot will therefore be
		able to handle new data in new schemas with no configuration.  The actual
		body of the data - is saved as a blob in the database and never touched or
		looked at by the depot.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	</itemizedList>
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>

<varListEntry>
<term><emphasis>Requirement:</emphasis>Data should be archived.</term>
<listItem>
<para>
	<itemizedList>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		All reporter data will be held in a relational database in a schema which
		will enable archiving.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	</itemizedList>
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>

<varListEntry>
<term><emphasis>Requirement:</emphasis> Data collected should not be lost due
to the failure of a single component.</term>
<listItem>
<para>
	<itemizedList>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		In the case that a depot is forwarding a report to another depot and the
		depot is not reachable it will be possible for the depot that posseses the
		report to log it and attempt the communication at a later point in time.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		In the case that a depot accumulates a large amount of logged interactions
		with another depot there will be a mechanism for attempting to notify a
		system administrator of the problem.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	</itemizedList>
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>

<varListEntry>
<term><emphasis>Requirement:</emphasis>Data pertaining to a single VO should
be available from a central location. </term>
<listItem>
<para>
	<itemizedList>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		A depot can be configured to forward queries to a set of depot's in order
		to make sure that all data pertaining to a query is retrieved.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		The results of a query across multiple depots are combined at the
		originating depot so the user is unaware that the data was distributed.
		</para>
	</listItem>
	<listItem>
		<para>
		The depots are all peers, any depot in a group can be contacted for
		information, there is no head depot.  
		</para>
	</listItem>
	</itemizedList>
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>

</variableList>

</section>
